gomodel:SYNGO_4680  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: This paper described ELFN2 as a new transsynaptic interactor of mGluR7. In Figure 1 evidence is provided that ELFN2 is present in synaptosomal preparations with high enrichment in the postsynaptic density fraction.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: from figure legend: \"Representative immunoblots for ELFN2 of subcellular fractionation of wild-type mouse brain\"\n\nantibody;\nELFN2, Sigma Cat#HPA000781 (1:1000)" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
